<h2>Gear List</h2>
<h3>What gear did I bring?</h3>

<p>
  Bikepacking is a unique combination of cycling and backpacking. When preparing for a multi-day race like the TransAtlanticWay, 
  every ounce matters. After many long training rides, I was able to hone in on the ideal gear list for the 8.5-day race, 
  keeping the total weight of everything, including the bike and bags, at 17.54kg.
</p>

<p>
  However, it's important to note that the amount of food and water on the bike would vary each day, depending on the route and 
  distance to the next resupply point. Despite this variable, I was confident that my meticulously selected gear list would 
  allow me to tackle the challenge ahead.
</p>

